s\nfor a mod. However, they often fail to do this in a systematic manner using the\nbug reporting tool of the Nexus Mods platform, resulting in low-quality bug\nreports which are difficult to resolve. Based on our findings, we recommend\nthat game developers who desire an active modding community for their own games\nprovide the modding community with an officially-supported modding tool. In\naddition, we recommend that mod distribution platforms, such as Nexus Mods,\nimprove their bug reporting system to receive higher quality bug reports.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Mar 2021 21:04:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-16"}
