we cannot rule out a possibility that the NRL\nmodel is simply imperfect in this region. We also present future prospects for\nthe upcoming Japan-US X-ray astronomy satellite, XRISM, which will allow us to\nmeasure atmospheric composition with unprecedented spectral resolution of dE ~\n5 eV in 0.3-12 keV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 13 Mar 2021 02:39:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-05"}
