gh {\\it Fermi}-LAT. The\nflare, decaying with $t^{-6/5}$ with a few months, will appear as a slowly\nvarying transient. The flares, occurring at a rate of a few per year in\nradio-quiet quasars, provide a new mechanism for explaining AGN variability.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 13 Mar 2021 12:31:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 10 Apr 2021 06:21:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-21"}
